@adavanisanti If you really want to use this library to send to S3 my best suggestion at the moment is to subclass the LoggingMixin to customize the needs of what you are looking for. Python has a S3 client (Boto I believe) You could even override the method's to not persist records at all.

If you felt inclined you could create a custom signal that could get called and listened to within the LoggingMixin, possibly even provide a setting to logically check to ignore persistence, you could even create a database router to send that model instances nowhere.

I welcome a PR to any of the above and I can take a look. :-)

