I think I've got a solution which only traces f forwards once (took a little while to work out how to do this!):

```python
def make_ggnvp(f, g=lambda x: 1./2*np.dot(x, x))
    def ggnvp(x):
         f_vjp, f_x = make_vjp(f)(x)
         g_hvp, grad_g_x = make_vjp(grad(g))(f_x)
         f_vjp_vjp, _ = make_vjp(f_vjp)(grad_g_x)
         return lambda v: f_vjp(g_hvp(f_vjp_vjp(v)))
    return ggnvp
```

