@pvanhorn, Thanks for sharing your concern.

Here we are talking about passing up ACK frame instead of a single `aFramPending` flag, there will be no changes to how radio receive packets, and no extra packets pool needed.

The radio could transmit only one packet at a time, it will not transmit the next packet until it receive the ACK or timeout. So only a single ACK packet will be used, but not a pool.

